Package com.deco2800.game.memento

Class PlayerMemento

java.lang.Object
com.deco2800.game.memento.PlayerMemento
public class PlayerMemento
extends java.lang.Object
Basic java memento object that is used as a storage to store player state. In general this object is immutable and it holds the internal state of hte originator and allows the originator to restore itself to an older version of itself

  • Constructor Details

    • PlayerMemento

      public PlayerMemento​(int id, int ammo, int gold, int bandage, int defenceLevel, int woundState, int baseRangedAttack, int baseAttack, int health, int bulletMagazine, java.lang.String ability, java.lang.String meleeFilePath, java.lang.String meleeWeaponType, java.lang.String armorType, double currentGameLevel, int torch)
      Creates a player memento object to be stored internally
      Parameters:
      id - that is unique and linked to originator created
      baseRangedAttack - amount of damage dealt by player via range
      baseAttack - amount of dadmage dealt by player via melee
      health - health of player in current state
      ammo - amount of ammo used for rnage attack
      bandage - used to heal player's wound state
      gold - amount of gold used to purchase items at player's current state
      woundState - wound state based on player's current state
      defenceLevel - of player in current state
      currentGameLevel - current game level of player's current state
      ability - being used in player's current state
      meleeFilePath - loads data relevant to melee weapon which will correspond to player's current state
      meleeWeaponType - weapon type of current player's state
      armorType - armor type of current player's state
      torch - the timer for the torch duration
